# .claude/ holds Claude Code session caches, project transcripts, local plans, etc.
# But a few subpaths are shared content used by every agent in this repo and
# MUST be tracked. Using /.claude/* (not .claude/) so git still descends into
# the dir to honor the negations below.
/.claude/*
!/.claude/skills/
!/.claude/hooks/
!/.claude/settings.json
*.swp
*.swo
*~

